folder: St. Raymond's Avenue & Olmstead Avenue, Bronx, NY
original_title: Bronx: St. Raymond's Avenue - Olmstead Avenue
text:
St. Raymond Avenue, north side, east from Olmstead Avenue. The three-story brick building is the service building of the Bronx Gas and Electric Company, at Odell Street.
April 10, 1938
P. L. Sperr

folder: Olmstead Avenue & St. Raymond Avenue, Bronx, NY
original_title: Bronx: Olmstead Avenue - St. Raymond Avenue
text:
Olmstead Avenue, at St. Raymond Avenue (vantage-point). The view is northeastward toward E. Tremont Avenue, across the area which will become part of the model housing development to be erected by the Metropolitan Life Insurance Company.
April 10, 1938
P. L. Sperr
